Handling missing values

Blood Pressure

hist(as.numeric(data$BloodPressureUpper),col="blue",border= "black",xlab = 
"BloodPressureUpper", ylab= "Counts", main = "Histogram of BloodPressureUpper")

upper_mean = mean(na.omit(as.numeric(data$BloodPressureUpper)))

upper_median = median(na.omit(as.numeric(data$BloodPressureUpper)))


upper_sd = sd(na.omit(as.numeric(data$BloodPressureUpper)))


upper_skew = (3 * (upper_mean - upper_median))/upper_sd
print(upper_skew)
## [1] 0.3834666
data$BloodPressureUpper[is.na(data$BloodPressureUpper)] = upper_mean
hist(as.numeric(data$BloodPressureDiff),col="blue",border= "black",xlab = 
"BloodPressureDiff", ylab= "Counts", main = "Histogram of BloodPressureDiff")

diff_mean = mean(na.omit(as.numeric(data$BloodPressureDiff)))

diff_median = median(na.omit(as.numeric(data$BloodPressureDiff)))


diff_sd = sd(na.omit(as.numeric(data$BloodPressureDiff)))


diff_skew = (3 * (diff_mean - diff_median))/diff_sd
print(diff_skew)
## [1] 0.3492178
data$BloodPressureDiff[is.na(data$BloodPressureDiff)] = diff_mean

Data Partitioning

# Dividing data into training and testing

set.seed(123)

# randomize dataset
data.randomize <- data[sample(nrow(data), replace = FALSE),]

# Determine the number of rows in your dataset
number_rows <- nrow(data.randomize)

# Calculate the number of rows for the training set (70%)
train_dataset <- round(0.7 * number_rows)

# Create the training and testing sets
data.train <- data.randomize[1:train_dataset, ]
data.test <- data.randomize[(train_dataset+1):number_rows,]
dim(data.train)
## [1] 778  15
dim(data.test)
## [1] 333  15

Balancing the dataset

table(data.train$Flipped)
## 
##   0   1 
## 420 358
library(ROSE)

data.train.bal <- ovun.sample(Flipped ~., data = data.train, p=0.5, method="both")

data.train.bal <-  data.train.bal$data
table(data.train.bal$Flipped)/nrow(data.train.bal)
## 
##         0         1 
## 0.4948586 0.5051414

Normalising the outliers

mi1 = min(data.train.bal$OU_LOS_hrs)
ma1 = max(data.train.bal$OU_LOS_hrs)
data.train.bal$OU_LOS_hrs = (data.train.bal$OU_LOS_hrs - mi1)/(ma1 - mi1)

data.test$OU_LOS_hrs = (data.test$OU_LOS_hrs - mi1)/(ma1 - mi1)
mi2 = min(data.train.bal$BloodPressureUpper)
ma2 = max(data.train.bal$BloodPressureUpper)
data.train.bal$BloodPressureUpper = (data.train.bal$BloodPressureUpper - mi2)/(ma2 - mi2)

data.test$BloodPressureUpper = (data.test$BloodPressureUpper - mi2)/(ma2 - mi2)
mi3 = min(data.train.bal$BloodPressureLower)
ma3 = max(data.train.bal$BloodPressureLower)
data.train.bal$BloodPressureLower = (data.train.bal$BloodPressureLower - mi3)/(ma3 - mi3)

data.test$BloodPressureLower = (data.test$BloodPressureLower - mi3)/(ma3 - mi3)
mi4 = min(data.train.bal$BloodPressureDiff)
ma4 = max(data.train.bal$BloodPressureDiff)
data.train.bal$BloodPressureDiff = (data.train.bal$BloodPressureDiff - mi4)/(ma4 - mi4)

data.test$BloodPressureDiff = (data.test$BloodPressureDiff - mi4)/(ma4 - mi4)
mi5 = min(data.train.bal$Pulse)
ma5 = max(data.train.bal$Pulse)
data.train.bal$Pulse = (data.train.bal$Pulse - mi5)/(ma5 - mi5)

data.test$Pulse = (data.test$Pulse - mi5)/(ma5 - mi5)
mi6 = min(data.train.bal$PulseOximetry)
ma6 = max(data.train.bal$PulseOximetry)
data.train.bal$PulseOximetry = (data.train.bal$PulseOximetry - mi6)/(ma6 - mi6)


data.test$PulseOximetry = (data.test$PulseOximetry - mi6)/(ma6 - mi6)
mi7 = min(data.train.bal$Respirations)
ma7 = max(data.train.bal$Respirations)
data.train.bal$Respirations = (data.train.bal$Respirations - mi7)/(ma7 - mi7)

data.test$Respirations = (data.test$Respirations - mi7)/(ma7 - mi7)
mi8 = min(data.train.bal$Temperature)
ma8 = max(data.train.bal$Temperature)
data.train.bal$Temperature = (data.train.bal$Temperature - mi8)/(ma8 - mi8)



data.test$Temperature = (data.test$Temperature - mi8)/(ma8 - mi8)
mi9 = min(data.train.bal$Age)
ma9 = max(data.train.bal$Age)
data.train.bal$Age = (data.train.bal$Age - mi9)/(ma9 - mi9)

data.test$Age = (data.test$Age - mi9)/(ma9 - mi9)

Methodology

# Full model with all predictors

model.null = lm(Flipped ~ 1 , data=data.train.bal)

model.full = lm(Flipped ~ Age + OU_LOS_hrs + DRG01 + BloodPressureUpper + BloodPressureLower + BloodPressureDiff + Pulse + PulseOximetry + Respirations + Temperature, data= data.train.bal)
reduced.forward.model = step(model.null, scope = list(lower = model.null, upper = model.full), direction = 
"forward", trace = FALSE) 
summary(reduced.forward.model)

Prediction for the Logistic Regression Model

## Loading required package: lattice
Predict_logitmodel <- predict(logistic_model, newdata = data.test, type = "response")

Predict_prob <- ifelse(Predict_logitmodel > 0.65, 1, 0)
